name: Jeff Wyler Nissan
description:
The charger on is located on the west side of the showroom. 2nd charger on small bldg south of 1st.
There is also a 3rd charger inside the service bay.

Sometimes the circuit is off. Just throw the switch on the wall behind the unit, and it will turn on.

name: Air Pollution Control District
description:
Single charger on the right as you pull in. It's hard to miss. Air pollution control district has a Ford Focus Electric plugged in occasionally, but always parked in one of the two EV spots, but I was told by an employee that it's ok to unplug it if it's finished charging.

Confirmed on July 12, 2019 by an employee that it’s acceptable to unplug the city owned Focus.  Charging is about 24A , 197v.  Model X / S Tesla will charge at about 14mi/hr.
